{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781418802,"nonce":"Qo1sgUInogpw8vvY9p4loEbQBQc=","title":"With the `uuid` feature enabled, `uuid::Uuid` has `Encode\u003cPostgres\u003e` / `Decode\u003cPostgres\u003e` (binding works). But using it idiomatically still hits two gaps:","message":"1. **`HasColumnType` missing** — a bare `uuid::Uuid` field does not compile; you must add `#[column(db_type = \"uuid\")]` to supply the DDL type. Ideally the field type alone should map to a `uuid` column (like `String` -\u003e `text`, `i64` -\u003e `bigint`), with no `db_type` override needed.\n2. **`ExprKind` missing (the blocker)** — even with `db_type = \"uuid\"`, a `Uuid` **value** cannot be used in the query builder: not as a predicate operand (`col.equals(some_uuid)`) and not as a write-builder setter (`.id(some_uuid)`), because `uuid::Uuid` doesn't implement `squealy::ExprKind`. Scalars (`String`, `i64`, `bool`) do, so `.equals(\"...\")` / `.id(42)` compile; `Uuid` does not, so every query keyed by a uuid column fails to compile.\n\n\nBare field (gap 1):\n\n```rust\nid: C::Type\u003c'scope, uuid::Uuid\u003e,   // error: `uuid::Uuid: HasColumnType` not satisfied\n```\n\nWorkaround for gap 1, then gap 2:\n\n```rust\nstruct Organization\u003c'scope, C: ColumnMode = ColumnExpr\u003e {\n    #[column(primary_key, db_type = \"uuid\")]   // db_type currently required\n    id: C::Type\u003c'scope, uuid::Uuid\u003e,\n    slug: C::Type\u003c'scope, String\u003e,\n}\n\nlet id: uuid::Uuid = /* ... */;\n\n// predicate operand:\nconn.from::\u003cOrganization\u003e()\n    .where_(|o| o.id.equals(id))\n    .select(|(o,)| o.slug)\n    .fetch_optional().await?;\n\n// write-builder setter:\nconn.to::\u003cOrganization\u003e().id(id).slug(\"acme\".to_owned()).insert().await?;\n```\n\n\n```\nerror[E0277]: the trait bound `uuid::Uuid: HasColumnType` is not satisfied   // without db_type\nerror[E0277]: the trait bound `uuid::Uuid: squealy::ExprKind` is not satisfied   // at every .equals(uuid) / .id(uuid)\n   --\u003e squealy/src/expr.rs:702\n```\n\nThe `ExprKind` failure then cascades: `.and(..)` on the resulting `Predicate`, `.select(..)`, and `.update()` / `.delete()` all report \"method exists but trait bounds were not satisfied\".\n\n\nUnder the `uuid` feature, `uuid::Uuid` should implement both:\n- `HasColumnType` (mapping to a `uuid` column), so no `db_type = \"uuid\"` override is needed; and\n- `ExprKind` (the value-as-expression side for literal predicate operands and setter values), like `String` / `i64` / `bool`.\n\n\nHard blocker for any schema with UUID keys. Encountered building the gitana catalog Postgres backend (UUID primary/foreign keys); every get/update/delete-by-id and uuid foreign-key insert is blocked.","files":null}]}